Let $\mathbf{a} = \begin{pmatrix} -3 \\ 9 \\ 11 \end{pmatrix},$ $\mathbf{b} = \begin{pmatrix} x \\ y \\ z \end{pmatrix},$ and $\mathbf{c} = \begin{pmatrix} 3 \\ 5 \\ 9 \end{pmatrix}.$  Then $\overrightarrow{AB} = \mathbf{b} - \mathbf{a}$ and $\overrightarrow{BC} = \mathbf{c} - \mathbf{b}.$

