label("$B$", B, S);
label("$C$", C, NE);
label("$\overrightarrow{AB}$", (A + B)/2, NW);
label("$\overrightarrow{BC}$", (B + C)/2, NE);
label("$\mathbf{n}$", (0,0,0.4*1.5), E);
[/asy]

Since $\overrightarrow{AB}$ and $\overrightarrow{BC}$ are reflections of each other across the plane, they make equal angles with the normal vector to the plane, $\mathbf{n} = \begin{pmatrix} 1 \\ 1 \\ 1 \end{pmatrix}.$  Hence,
\[\frac{\overrightarrow{AB} \cdot \mathbf{n}}{||\overrightarrow{AB}||} = \frac{\overrightarrow{BC} \cdot \mathbf{n}}{||\overrightarrow{BC}||}.\]This simplifies to
\[\frac{\begin{pmatrix} x + 3 \\ y - 9 \\ z - 11 \end{pmatrix} \cdot \begin{pmatrix} 1 \\ 1 \\ 1 \end{pmatrix}}{\left\| \begin{pmatrix} x + 3 \\ y - 9 \\ z - 11 \end{pmatrix} \right\|} = \frac{\begin{pmatrix} 3 - x \\ 5 - y \\ 9 - z \end{pmatrix} \cdot \begin{pmatrix} 1 \\ 1 \\ 1 \end{pmatrix}}{\left\| \begin{pmatrix} 3 - x \\ 5 - y \\ 9 - z \end{pmatrix} \right\|}.\]Then
\[\frac{x + y + z - 7}{\sqrt{(x + 3)^2 + (y - 9)^2 + (z - 11)^2}} = \frac{17 - x - y - z}{\sqrt{(3 - x)^2 + (5 - y)^2 + (9 - z)^2}}.\]Squaring both sides, we get
\[\frac{(x + y + z - 7)^2}{(x + 3)^2 + (y - 9)^2 + (z - 11)^2} = \frac{(17 - x - y - z)^2}{(3 - x)^2 + (5 - y)^2 + (9 - z)^2}.\]Cross-multiplying, we get
\[(x + y + z - 7)^2 [(3 - x)^2 + (5 - y)^2 + (9 - z)^2] = (17 - x - y - z)^2 [(x + 3)^2 + (y - 9)^2 + (z - 11)^2].\]Expanding, we get
\begin{align*}
&(x + y + z - 7)^2 [(3 - x)^2 + (5 - y)^2 + (9 - z)^2] \\
&\quad = (17 - x - y - z)^2 [(x + 3)^2 + (y - 9)^2 + (z - 11)^2] \\
&\quad = (x + y + z - 17)^2 [(x + 3)^2 + (y - 9)^2 + (z - 11)^2].
\end{align*}Since $B$ lies on the plane $x + y + z = 12,$ $x + y + z = 12,$ so
\[(12 - 7)^2 [(3 - x)^2 + (5 - y)^2 + (9 - z)^2] = (12 - 17)^2 [(x + 3)^2 + (y - 9)^2 + (z - 11)^2].\]This simplifies to
\[25 [(3 - x)^2 + (5 - y)^2 + (9 - z)^2] = 25 [(x + 3)^2 + (y - 9)^2 + (z - 11)^2].\]Then
\[(3 - x)^2 + (5 - y)^2 + (9 - z)^2 = (x + 3)^2 + (y - 9)^2 + (z - 11)^2.\]Expanding, we get
\[9 - 6x + x^2 + 25 - 10y + y^2 + 81 - 18z + z^2 = x^2 + 6x + 9 + y^2 - 18y + 81 + z^2 - 22z + 121.\]This simplifies to $12x + 8y + 4z = 107.$  Along with the equation $x + y + z = 12,$ we can solve to get $x = \frac{19}{3},$ $y = \frac{23}{3},$ and $z = \frac{10}{3}.$

